    "recap_headline": "Lehigh University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "BETHLEHEM, Pa.\u00a0\u2013 Lehigh baseball opened Patriot League play on Friday afternoon from J. David Walker Field against the Navy Midshipmen. Stellar performances on the mound from starter\nSam Fairhurst\nand reliever\nChristopher Nell\nguided the Mountain Hawks to a 3-1 victory over the Mids.\nFairhurst earned the win for Lehigh (4-10, 1-0 PL), striking out seven batters while allowing four hits and one earned run in 5.0 innings pitched. Nell impressed with five strikeouts with only one hit in 4.0 scoreless innings. Navy starter Brady Bendik was credited with the loss despite a solid stat line of ten strikeouts with six hits and three earned runs in 7.0 complete innings.\nFairhurst and Bendik made quick work through the first two innings, as both pitchers only faced eight batter through the first and second innings. The Mountain Hawks broke the tie in the bottom of the third, plating three runs on RBIs from\nRaffaele Rogers\n,\nAidan Quinn\n, and\nRyan Cochran\n. Fairhurst then retired the side 1-2-3 in the top of the fourth inning.\nAfter several great innings from Fairhurst and Bendik, the Mids finally got on the board in the top of the sixth when Ty DePerno grounded into a double play that scored Mason Ceccarelli. Nell entered the game and limited Navy to only one run in the frame, keeping the score at 3-1. The Mids generated runners on third and first in the eighth, but Nell got the outs necessary to keep Navy off the board. A 1-2-3 inning in the top of the ninth for the first-year sealed Lehigh's league-opening victory.\nQuinn finished the day going 2-3 with a walk and an RBI.\nDom Patrizi\n,\nOwen Walewander\n,\nSilvio Giardina\n, and Rogers also recorded hits for the Mountain Hawks.\nThe Mountain Hawks return to J. David Walker Field for game two of the series on Saturday, March 14 at 1 p.m.\nLike Lehigh Baseball on\nFacebook\n, follow on\nX\n(formerly Twitter)\u00a0and\nInstagram\nfor exclusive content, team updates and more."
